theorem Topology.P1_preimage
    {X Y : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y]
    {f : X → Y} (hf : Continuous f) {B : Set Y} (hB : Topology.P1 B) :
    Topology.P1 (f ⁻¹' B) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hB ⊢
  intro x hx
  -- `f x` lies in `B`
  have h_fxB : f x ∈ B := hx
  -- From `P1` for `B`, `f x` belongs to the closure of the interior of `B`
  have h_fx_cl : f x ∈ closure (interior B) := hB h_fxB
  -- Translate this membership via the preimage
  have h_pre : (x : X) ∈ f ⁻¹' closure (interior B) := h_fx_cl
  -- Continuity turns the preimage of a closure into a subset of the closure of a preimage
  have h_pre_subset :
      f ⁻¹' closure (interior B) ⊆ closure (f ⁻¹' interior B) :=
    hf.preimage_closure _
  have h_x_cl_pre : x ∈ closure (f ⁻¹' interior B) :=
    h_pre_subset h_pre
  -- The set `f ⁻¹' interior B` is an open subset of `f ⁻¹' B`
  have h_open_pre : IsOpen (f ⁻¹' interior B) :=
    (isOpen_interior : IsOpen (interior B)).preimage hf
  have h_subset_pre :
      (f ⁻¹' interior B : Set X) ⊆ interior (f ⁻¹' B) :=
    interior_maximal
      (Set.preimage_mono (interior_subset : interior B ⊆ B))
      h_open_pre
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions
  have h_closure_mono :
      closure (f ⁻¹' interior B) ⊆ closure (interior (f ⁻¹' B)) :=
    closure_mono h_subset_pre
  exact h_closure_mono h_x_cl_pre

theorem Topology.interiorClosure_idempotent
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure A))) = interior (closure A) := by
  -- First inclusion: `interior (closure (interior (closure A))) ⊆ interior (closure A)`.
  have h₁ : interior (closure (interior (closure A))) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
    have hsubset : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A :=
      closure_mono (interior_subset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A)
    exact interior_mono hsubset
  -- Second inclusion: `interior (closure A) ⊆ interior (closure (interior (closure A)))`.
  have h₂ : interior (closure A) ⊆ interior (closure (interior (closure A))) := by
    have hsubset : (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
      subset_closure
    exact interior_maximal hsubset isOpen_interior
  -- Combine the inclusions to obtain the desired equality.
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem Topology.P3_of_P3_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 (closure A) → Topology.P3 A := by
  intro hP3
  dsimp [Topology.P3] at hP3 ⊢
  intro x hx
  -- Since `x ∈ A`, we have `x ∈ closure A`.
  have hx_closure : (x : X) ∈ closure A := subset_closure hx
  -- From `P3 (closure A)`, we know `closure A ⊆ interior (closure (closure A))`.
  have h_subset : (closure A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (closure A)) := hP3
  -- Hence `x` lies in `interior (closure (closure A))`.
  have hx_int : (x : X) ∈ interior (closure (closure A)) := h_subset hx_closure
  -- But `closure (closure A)` is just `closure A`.
  simpa [closure_closure] using hx_int
